CLAIM.OWNER: Branch William A Buster Jr William C and Cohen Mark

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANTASTIC settled in the two path while in range, was coaxed along but was boxed in on the far turn, found an opening leaving the bend, split foes and bumped inner rival at the top of the stretch, took over and cleared nearing the eighth pole, widened through the final furlong and was in hand approaching the wire. BALADI got bumped from inside leaving the gate, was reserved at the back and moved inside, trailed to the far turn, swung out leaving the bend and top of the stretch, closed well in the drive and bested the rest. READY SOUL broke out and bumped BALADI, raced up close outside the pacesetter, took aim three wide into the lane, lacked the needed response to threaten the winner but kept on to earn the show honors. IT'S MY HOUSE sped to the front and took control of the rail, showed the way to the far turn, asked right handed leaving the bend and continued clear three wide into the stretch, was overtaken and chased VANTASTIC into the final furlong, then flattened and was outfinished for the place and show. NEPTUNE'S STORM stalked the pace along the rail, cut the corner into the lane, got bumped and crowded by the winner in upper stretch and could not rally after. MOODY JIM (IRE) raced along the three path stalking the pace early on, spun four wide into the stretch and lacked further response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHARED FUTURE away well from inside and chased the leader into the first turn, switched to the outside around the clubhouse turn to stalk, applied pressure from outside up the backstretch, dueled around the far turn and into the lane, put a nose in front in midstretch and dug in to inch ahead late. BIG SWITCH went up to take the lead from outside and crossed over to the rail on the first turn, set the pace under pressure in the middle stages, dueled with SHARED FUTURE around the far turn, maintained a short lead to the eighth pole, was overtaken shortly after but fought back from inside and stayed on gamely to the line. TROUVILLE bobbled leaving the gate, took back when crowded briefly between rivals, tucked inside on the first turn, eased out on the far turn and chased three wide into the drive but could not find the needed late kick in the late stages. MICRO SHARE was off a bit slow to start, trailed three wide into the first turn, moved a bit closer up the backstretch, angled to the rail on the far turn and failed to menace. ALOHA KITTEN stumbled leaving the gate, chased three wide around both turns and weakened. GLORY OF CHROME forwardly placed between rivals then chased two to three wide on the first turn, dropped back to last on the backstretch, weakened around the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNWRITTEN CODE hustled to the front, set the pace under pressure from outer rival early, disposed of that foe into the turn, saved ground through the bend, roused in upper stretch and drew off under mild urging. TRICKLE IN chased the speed outside a rival, rounded the bend in the two path, tipped out at the top of the stretch and bested the rest. INVINCIBELLA (GB) allowed to settle at the back early, got bumped three deep into the turn, driven two wide into the stretch, angled out in the stretch and nailed KEEP YOUR COIL for the show honors. KEEP YOUR COIL popped the stall open, was backed out and reloaded, stalked the top pair up the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, failed to find the needed late kick and got nailed for third. MIRACLE OF HOPE chased at the back off the rail then between rivals leaving the backstretch, got bumped on both sides then put in tight early on the turn, shifted over to the rail around the bend, altered out from behind a rival in upper stretch and failed to menace. PIAZZETTA was a bit erratic in the early going, went up to press the pace from outside, could not keep pace and chased the leader into and around the turn from the two path, continued to race a bit erratic in the lane and weakened between foes. SOARING SKY (IRE) was off a bit slow from inside, tracked along the rail then bumped outer rival and steadied at the three furlong point, angled out and came three wide into the stretch and could not rally. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM'S X S was off slow in the beginning, steered to the outside chasing the top quartet, challenged four then three deep around the bend, took over nearing the stretch, kicked clear in upper stretch and held well late. CAROL'S COMIC stalked off the rail, navigated the turn three wide, moved out four wide in upper stretch, finished determinedly and closed ground late on the winner. MAGNIFICENT RIDE broke a step slow on the outside, went up to vie for the lead four deep, fought for command three then two wide around the bend, flattened in the drive and walked into the van following the race. AGADOR SPARTACUS chased off the rail then climbed a bit and was taken out wider while dropping back to last, took the turn three then four wide and failed to menace. IRONDALE broke a step slow, went up to press then vied inside a trio of rivals into the turn, got bumped and checked hard nearing three-eighths pole, continued along the fence to the stretch and was ridden out through the lane. CHIEF COUNCIL vied for the lead three deep up the backstretch, challenged between rivals then started to weaken around the bend, tired and eased in the final furlong and walked off. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED SIX FEET FROM FOURTH TO SIXTH FOR DRIFTING IN AND BUMPING IRONDALE EARLY ON THE TURN, CAUSING THAT RIVAL TO CHECK HARD AND COST HIM A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ITZEL sped clear and set the pace up the backstretch, showed the way along the inside around the bend, met the challenge from FOOLISH past the quarter pole, bumped with that rival in upper stretch, maintained a short lead into the final sixteenth and dug down deep to shake free from the runner-up late. FOOLISH was off a bit slow and shifted in, had to pause behind a rival then moved out early, was on the move while angling down to the inside then steered out to bid outside ITZEL past the quarter pole, bumped with that rival in upper stretch, kept the pressure on entering deep stretch but was turned away late. CALIFORNIA BLING tracked the pace on the inside, steered out in upper stretch and rallied for the show. CASINO ANNIE got crowded between rivals and steadied early, raced two wide around the bend, angled out into the stretch and missed third. PRINCESS MAGIC broke a step slow, pulled the rider to a forward position then had to steady at the seven-sixteenths pole, tipped two wide then got floated out to the three path by FOOLISH late on the turn and weakened in the stretch run. SMART KITTEN broke in and brushed rival, stalked three deep into the turn, spun four wide into the lane and weakened. ALWAYS CALIFORNIA got brushed leaving the gate, stalked between rivals into the turn, went two then three wide around the turn and weakened. RYLAN JAYNE brushed at the start, got crowded between rivals early, pulled up on the turn and walked off. RACE ORIGINALLY HAND-TIMED, TIMES CHANGED FOLLOWING REVIEW.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE GREY WIZARD (IRE) got bumped in the beginning, reserved early on and moved inside, waited for room on the far turn, tipped out and launched a bid between rivals while bumping REMOTE past the eighth pole, took over in midstretch and drew away under hand urging. AJAAWEED raced up close then chased to the outside of the leader early on, challenged from outside at the seven-sixteenths pole, duelded around the far turn, fought the rider changing leads in upper stretch, switched to the correct lead then took over briefly past the eighth pole, was overtaken by the winner shortly after and stayed on to secure second. BENDER settled at the back in the two path, went between foes on the far turn, spun three wide into the lane, angled out widest in the drive and got up for third. REMOTE got bumped leaving the gate, forwardly placed down the hill and got bumped on both sides crossing over the dirt, took a stalking position between rivals, moved out in upper stretch, bid and got bumped by the winner past the eighth pole and faltered in deep stretch. AGATINO (IRE) broke out and bumped rival, lugged out and bumped crossing over the dirt then checked between rivals, angled down to the inside to stalk the pace, waited for room behind the leader on the far turn, tried to rallied but never found room through the lane and had to check late. DOMINANT SOUL broke out, went up to take control from inside, challenged at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled around the far turn, lost command after passing the eighth pole and weakened in deep stretch.
